There are people who still believe they’d be able to cheat lockdown regulations in Mzansi. Gauteng community MEC Faith Mazibuko said the cops arrested a man who was trying to smuggle his girlfriend into Gauteng without permit. She tweeted: A man was arrested at the N12 roadblock on Friday, 17 April, for attempting to smuggle his girlfriend out of GP to MP, without a permit. “Law enforcement asked the man to open the boot to search, they found a lady inside. “She was also arrested for agreeing to being smuggled.” 